# Running Tests

Always run Playwright from the project root. **The browser must be visible** (headed mode): pass `--headed` on the CLI, or use `npm run test:headed`, or `npm run test:graf -- --headed`, so a real browser window opens. Do not run the suite headless when executing tests on behalf of the user unless they explicitly ask for headless.

```bash
cd /Users/acortes/git/turnitin_tests_playwright && npx playwright test --headed [path|pattern] [options]
```

- **Working directory**: `/Users/acortes/git/turnitin_tests_playwright`
- **Test directory** (configured in `playwright.config.ts`): `src/tests/`
- **Environment**: load `.env` in the project root; `baseURL` uses `TII_URL`.

## npm scripts

- `npm test` — full suite, **headless** (avoid for interactive runs; prefer `npm run test:headed` or add `-- --headed`)
- `npm run test:headed` — full suite with visible browser
- `npm run test:debug` — Playwright inspector (visible)
- `npm run test:graf` — Graf-related specs (`instructor-graf` filter); add `--headed` if the script does not already pass it: `npm run test:graf -- --headed`

## Examples

Run one spec file:

```bash
cd /Users/acortes/git/turnitin_tests_playwright && npx playwright test --headed src/tests/instructor-graf.spec.ts
```

Run a single test by title (grep):

```bash
cd /Users/acortes/git/turnitin_tests_playwright && npx playwright test --headed -g "exact or partial title"
```

Chromium project (default from config):

```bash
cd /Users/acortes/git/turnitin_tests_playwright && npx playwright test --headed --project=chromium
```
